b. Find the probability that a randomly selected student scored less than 85 .

\section*{(1) Solution}
a. Let $X=$ a score on the final exam. $X \sim N(63,5)$, where $\mu=63$ and $\sigma=5$.

Draw a graph.
Then, find $P(x>65)$.
$P(x>65)=0.3446$

\begin{figure}
\includegraphics[alt={},max width=\textwidth]{./images/d6af213e-1be7-45b3-b40f-841039940c99-293_751_743_1628_691.jpg}
\captionsetup{labelformat=empty}
\caption{Figure 6.6}
